<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Sim_Paying_Bills" s="74078">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0x8C815F64<!--String: "Paying Bills"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Paying_Bills_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:de073268c83771bc</T>
      <T n="text">0xACC0CAAA<!--String: "Bills arrive in the mailbox. They can be paid via the computer, your phone, or on the mailbox.\n\nYou will get a notification reminder before your bills become late."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Paying_Bills_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:de073268c83771bf</T>
      <T n="text">0xA443D831<!--String: "As Sims buy more items and increase the value of their home, their bills will increase. Bills are primarily comprised of a tax on the lot’s value as well as the utility usage of objects in the form of Power and Water. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Paying_Bills_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:de073268c83771be</T>
      <T n="text">0x34CFFCE9<!--String: "Not paying bills will result in the possible loss of your utilities, such as Power and Water. If bills remain delinquent long enough the Repo Person will arrive and take objects to pay off any debts. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Paying_Bills_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:de073268c83771b9</T>
      <T n="text">0xCCBD00F8<!--String: "Click the “Show Bills Information” interaction on any mailbox to view additional information pertaining to Bills and Utilities. Hover over any line item title in the Current Billing Estimate section of the menu to learn what is affecting your upcoming bill. See the current estimate to the right."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Paying_Bills_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:de073268c83771b8</T>
      <T n="text">0x4397CFD0<!--String: "Additional Power or Water utility that the player generates for the week is detailed on the right side of this menu. These utilities are automatically set to Auto Sell and will deduct from the weekly bill when it arrives. Toggling them to Store will allow the player to accrue Power or Water until a cap is reached. Excess Power or Water utility may be sold at any time by pressing the Sell Now button."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_MoneyWork</E>
